b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":2210,"category_name":"Events","pr_category_id":"4","title_name":"The Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes Event Was Added to the Event Compendium!","message":"<div>The Fire Emblem: Lost Heroes event was added to the available events in the event compendium at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1621231200\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><a href=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.com\/en\/news\/detail\/1176\\">See here for details about the event compendium.<\/a><\/div><div><img src=\\"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/76e6b95011253c53d2a5ab5627f1265b.png\\"><\/div><div>Heroes from another world are thrust into the world of Dragalia Lost! As two princes clash, a bewitching emissary launches an attack with the Imperial army. It&#39;s the power to open otherworldly gates versus dragonblood in this meeting of two realms. With Heroes, motivations, and alliances intertwined, what will become of this world?<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Adventurer<\/div><div>As you progress through the story for this event, the 5\\u2605 adventurer Alfonse will join your team.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Repel the Empire!<\/div><div>This quest pits you against the Dyrenell Empire, and can be played in co-op. It comes in four difficulty levels: Normal, Hard, Lunatic, and Infernal. Infernal difficulty will unlock as you progress through the event story. The rewards for this quest vary based on the difficulty.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Trial Quests<\/div><div>These challenging quests are unlocked by clearing certain other quests. There are two quests: Alfonse&#39;s Trial and Veronica&#39;s Trial.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0The Alberian Front<\/div><div>In this quest, you&#39;ll protect your gate from advancing Dyrenell Empire forces. You can clear it by either protecting the gate for a certain amount of time or defeating the Imperial Commander. It comes in three difficulty levels: Normal, Hard, and Lunatic. Each difficulty level will unlock as you progress through the event story. The rewards for this quest vary based on the difficulty.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Valor Rewards<\/div><div>Valor points are points that can be earned by clearing event quests. Collect them to earn all kinds of rewards!<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Treasure Trade Rewards<\/div><div>You can trade badges and great badges from event quests for various rewards.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Badges and Great badges<\/div><div>You can earn badges and great badges by clearing event quests.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Event Bonus<\/div><div>The following wyrmprints will have bonus effects during this event.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Order&#39;s Messenger Owl<\/div><div>\\u30fbA Brief Repose<\/div><div>\\u30fbThe Heroes Arrive<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>If you equip these wyrmprints and clear event quests, you&#39;ll get even more valor points. The amount of event bonus effect differs based on the wyrmprint and how much the wyrmprint has been unbound.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0Notes<\/div><div>\\u30fbAll quests added this time are solo-only quests and cannot be played in co-op.<\/div><div>\\u30fbMore events will be made available in future updates.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div>","start_time":1621231200,"prev_article_id":"2185","next_article_id":"2211","image_path":"https:\/\/dragalialost.akamaized.net\/attached\/information\/images\/76e6b95011253c53d2a5ab5627f1265b.png","update_time":1621222094}}}'